<para><variablelist>
<varlistentry><term>Refines</term></varlistentry>
<listitem><para><computeroutput><ref refid="classMeshDomain__3" kindref="compound" external="/home/runner/work/cgal-cn/cgal-cn/build_doc/doc_tags/Mesh_3.tag">MeshDomain_3</ref></computeroutput> </para>
</listitem>
</variablelist>
</para>
<para>The concept <computeroutput><ref refid="classPeriodic__3MeshDomain__3" kindref="compound">Periodic_3MeshDomain_3</ref></computeroutput> describes the knowledge required on the object to be discretized. The concept <computeroutput><ref refid="classPeriodic__3MeshDomain__3" kindref="compound">Periodic_3MeshDomain_3</ref></computeroutput> is the concept to be used when the input domain is defined over the three-dimensional flat torus.</para>
<para>From a syntactic point of view, it defines almost the same requirements as the concept <computeroutput><ref refid="classMeshDomain__3" kindref="compound" external="/home/runner/work/cgal-cn/cgal-cn/build_doc/doc_tags/Mesh_3.tag">MeshDomain_3</ref></computeroutput> and thus <computeroutput><ref refid="classPeriodic__3MeshDomain__3" kindref="compound">Periodic_3MeshDomain_3</ref></computeroutput> refines <computeroutput><ref refid="classMeshDomain__3" kindref="compound" external="/home/runner/work/cgal-cn/cgal-cn/build_doc/doc_tags/Mesh_3.tag">MeshDomain_3</ref></computeroutput>: the concept <computeroutput><ref refid="classPeriodic__3MeshDomain__3" kindref="compound">Periodic_3MeshDomain_3</ref></computeroutput> additionally requires an access to the user-defined canonical cuboid via the function <computeroutput>bounding_box</computeroutput>. However, the oracle must take into account the periodicity of the domain (see Section <ref refid="index_1Periodic_3_mesh_3InputDomain" kindref="member">Input Domain</ref>).</para>
<para>The class <computeroutput><ref refid="classCGAL_1_1Labeled__mesh__domain__3" kindref="compound" external="/home/runner/work/cgal-cn/cgal-cn/build_doc/doc_tags/Mesh_3.tag">CGAL::Labeled_mesh_domain_3</ref>&lt;BGT&gt;</computeroutput> paired with a periodic labeling function is a model of this concept. It is possible to create artificially periodic functions through the class <computeroutput><ref refid="classCGAL_1_1Periodic__3__function__wrapper" kindref="compound">CGAL::Periodic_3_function_wrapper</ref>&lt;Function,BGT&gt;</computeroutput>.</para>
